Overcast with winds from the east-southeast.
Sunny and windy past few days.
Same- yellow water lilies blooming- filamentous algae near shore and spring.
I was surprised that the lake was still so turbid since Lake Monona had algae level substantially down from July.
Cloudy water- not as nice as I remember from last year.
Shoreline plants choked with brown scum.
Shoreline plants choked with brown scum.
Lake seemed unchanged from spring to fall.
Overcast- mild wind from SE- low relative humidity
Heron and flyfisherman along shore. Sunny- approx. 70 F- cool breeze- a few boats on the lake. Satellite date.

Sunny- clear blue skies- fairly calm.  Atrazine sample.  A sailboat- a few kayaks- canoes and rowboats.  Several people fly fishing.  Water green- but clear.  Water color against secchi disc yellowish green.
some wind- challenge to stay on station

Clear skies- calm winds- water a brownish color

Partly sunny skies- light winds (4 mph)- very green water
Wind about 5 mph- sunny by overcast- very green water
Blue skies- light wind- green color
